Support for FLIR Imaging (formerly Point Grey Research) spinnaker camera library.
This library supercedes the flycapture2 library for USB3 and GigE cameras.

When building on a clean mac, the library is not found after building quip:

spin.lucia <36> ./quip
dyld[46897]: Library not loaded: libSpinVideo_C.dylib.3.2.0.62
  Referenced from: <8AAB568F-BBB3-3544-BF99-842EE68F53AC> /Users/larsinte/jbm/working/quip/src/quip
  Reason: tried: 'libSpinVideo_C.dylib.3.2.0.62' (no such file), '/System/Volumes/Preboot/Cryptexes/OSlibSpinVideo_C.dylib.3.2.0.62' (no such file), 'libSpinVideo_C.dylib.3.2.0.62' (no such file), '/Users/larsinte/jbm/working/quip/src/libSpinVideo_C.dylib.3.2.0.62' (no such file), '/System/Volumes/Preboot/Cryptexes/OS/Users/larsinte/jbm/working/quip/src/libSpinVideo_C.dylib.3.2.0.62' (no such file), '/Users/larsinte/jbm/working/quip/src/libSpinVideo_C.dylib.3.2.0.62' (no such file)
Abort trap: 6


An environment variable must be set to tell quip where to find the library...
The libraries are located in /Applications/Spinnaker/lib

